Steps to create separate exe file for every program

Step1:
Write the program

$gedit hello.c

#include<stdio.h>
void main()
{
  		printf("Hello World");
}

Step2:
Compile the program and generate .obj file

$cc –c hello.c

Result file is “hello.o”

Step3
Create exe file

$cc –o  <result_exe_name>  <obj_file1, obj_file2,obj_file3........>

$cc –o hello  hello.o

$ls
hello.c  hello.o  hello

Step4:
Execution

$./hello

